article.headline: Sacred Heart defeats Dartmouth 67-57
article.description: — Joey Reilly had 19 points in Sacred Heart's 67-57 win against Dartmouth on Thursday.
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- — Joey Reilly had 19 points in Sacred Heart's 67-57 win against Dartmouth on Thursday. Reilly was 6 of 11 shooting, including 3 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Pioneers (5-9). Kyle McGee scored 15 points while shooting 5 of 6 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line. Nico Galette had 14 points and went 7 of 17 from the field. The Pioneers stopped a seven-game skid with the win. Dusan Neskovic finished with 19 points for the Big Green (4-8). Brandon Mitchell-Day added 14 points, six rebounds, two steals and two blocks for Dartmouth. Ryan Cornish also had nine points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
